{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895645804,"sessionID":"ses_28462a26bffeq8oXJ4B2HFgoq1","part":{"id":"prt_d7b9d74d7001JDfW4GM8OsfEHy","messageID":"msg_d7b9d697e001nN3HkhdE3WKujW","sessionID":"ses_28462a26bffeq8oXJ4B2HFgoq1","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_0d5b4d87e456455cae8f42ad","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project at /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure - list top-level directories and key subdirectories\n2. Look at the test/ directory structure if it exists\n3. Find any existing test files (unit tests, integration tests, e2e tests)\n4. Look at the main application code structure - controllers, APIs, types\n5. Find any existing design documents or architecture docs\n6. Look at go.mod to understand dependencies\n7. Find any Makefile targets related to testing\n8. Look at the pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1 types definitions\n9. Check for any existing e2e test patterns or frameworks used\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of:\n- Project structure overview\n- Existing test infrastructure\n- Key types and APIs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n- Testing frameworks/patterns already in use\n- Any relevant configuration files\n- Controller/manager structure","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_28462749fffe24OuNK046Kmx0L (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nNow I have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Here is the full summary:\n\n---\n\n## AgentCube Project -- Comprehensive Analysis\n\n### 1. Project Structure Overview\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/\n├── cmd/                          # Binary entry points (5 binaries)\n│   ├── agentd/                   # Idle cleanup controller\n│   ├── cli/                      # CLI tool (Python-based)\n│   ├── picod/                    # PicoD code execution daemon\n│   ├── router/                   # HTTP reverse proxy / load balancer\n│   └── workloadmanager/          # Control plane API server\n├── pkg/                          # Go library packages\n│   ├── agentd/                   # Idle cleanup reconciler\n│   ├── apis/                     # Kubernetes API type definitions\n│   │   ├── agents/v1alpha1/      # Sandbox CRD types\n│   │   └── runtime/v1alpha1/     # CodeInterpreter + AgentRuntime CRD types\n│   ├── common/                   # Shared utilities\n│   ├── picod/                    # PicoD server, execution, file handling\n│   ├── router/                   # Router: proxy, JWT auth, load balancing\n│   ├── store/                    # Session store (Redis + Valkey backends)\n│   └── workloadmanager/          # Handler, middleware, reconciler, response\n├── client-go/                    # Generated Kubernetes clientset, listers, informers\n├── python-sdk/                   # Python SDK (agentcube package)\n├── integrations/                 # Dify plugin integration\n├── manifests/                    # Helm charts + CRDs\n│   └── charts/base/              # Main Helm chart\n├── docker/                       # Dockerfiles (Dockerfile, Dockerfile.router, Dockerfile.picod)\n├── deployment/                   # Deployment design docs\n├── test/                         # Test scripts (chart rendering, Makefile tests)\n├── testing/                      # TDD manifest\n├── hack/                         # Code generation scripts (update-codegen.sh)\n├── .github/workflows/            # CI/CD pipelines\n├── example/                      # PCAP Analyzer example app\n├── Makefile                      # Build, test, docker, lint targets\n├── go.mod                        # Go module: github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube (Go 1.25.0)\n├── design.md                     # Python SDK test design document\n├── proposal.md                   # Dify plugin integration proposal\n├── delta-spec.md                 # Spec deltas\n├── tasks.md                      # Task tracking\n└── test_spec.md                  # Test specifications\n```\n\n### 2. Existing Test Infrastructure\n\n#### Go Unit Tests (35 test files found)\nAll use the standard `go test` framework with `github.com/stretchr/testify` (assert/require):\n\n| Package | Test Files | Coverage Areas |\n|---------|-----------|----------------|\n| `pkg/router/` | 9 files | Router, backend, loadbalancer, JWT, middleware, health, config, errors, server |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/` | 5 files | Handler (models, sandbox_lifecycle, sandbox_delete), reconciler (fixtures, metrics), response |\n| `pkg/agentd/` | 1 file | Reconciler (idle cleanup) |\n| `pkg/picod/` | 7 files | Server, execute, auth, config, health, sanitize, files (read, write, manager, sanitize) |\n| `pkg/store/` | 4 files | Redis store, Valkey store, codec, singleton |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` | 5 files | CodeInterpreter types, AgentRuntime types, shared types, constants, groupversion info |\n\n#### Python Tests (8 test files in `python-sdk/tests/`)\nUses **pytest** with `unittest.mock`:\n\n| Test File | Coverage |\n|-----------|----------|\n| `test_code_interpreter.py` | CodeInterpreterClient (high-level facade) |\n| `test_data_plane.py` | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient |\n| `test_control_plane.py` | ControlPlaneClient |\n| `test_agent_runtime.py` | AgentRuntimeClient + AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient |\n| `test_utils.py` | HTTP utils, token reading, logging |\n| `test_exceptions.py` | Exception hierarchy |\n| `test_imports.py` | Package imports and `__all__` |\n| `conftest.py` | Shared fixtures |\n\n#### Integration/E2E Tests\n- **E2E workflow**: `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` -- uses **Kind cluster** (v0.30.0), runs `make e2e` (references `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` which does NOT exist yet)\n- **CLI e2e test**: `cmd/cli/tests/integration/test_build_e2e.py` -- pytest-based, tests CLI build command with mocked Docker\n- **Chart test**: `test/chart/test_render.sh` -- Bash script with 50+ assertions validating Helm chart rendering\n- **Makefile test**: `test/makefile/test_makefile.sh` -- Bash script with 25 test cases validating all Makefile targets\n\n### 3. Key Types and APIs\n\n#### CRD Group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n\n**CodeInterpreter** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`):\n```go\ntype CodeInterpreter struct {\n    Spec   CodeInterpreterSpec\n    Status CodeInterpreterStatus\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n    Ports              []TargetPort\n    Template           *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate  // Pod template\n    SessionTimeout     *metav1.Duration                 // default 15m\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration                 // default 8h\n    WarmPoolSize       *int32                           // optional warm pool\n    AuthMode           AuthModeType                     // \"picod\" | \"none\"\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate struct {\n    Labels, Annotations  map[string]string\n    RuntimeClassName     *string\n    Image                string\n    ImagePullPolicy      corev1.PullPolicy\n    ImagePullSecrets     []corev1.LocalObjectReference\n    Environment          []corev1.EnvVar\n    Command, Args        []string\n    Resources            corev1.ResourceRequirements\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition\n    Ready      bool\n}\n```\n\n**AgentRuntime** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agent_type.go`):\n```go\ntype AgentRuntime struct {\n    Spec   AgentRuntimeSpec\n    Status AgentRuntimeStatus\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n    Ports              []TargetPort\n    Template           *SandboxTemplate       // Full PodSpec\n    SessionTimeout     *metav1.Duration\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration\n}\n\ntype SandboxTemplate struct {\n    Labels, Annotations map[string]string\n    Spec                corev1.PodSpec        // Full K8s PodSpec\n}\n```\n\n**Shared Types** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go`):\n```go\ntype ProtocolType string   // \"HTTP\" | \"HTTPS\"\ntype AuthModeType string   // \"picod\" | \"none\"\ntype TargetPort struct {\n    PathPrefix string\n    Name       string\n    Port       uint32\n    Protocol   ProtocolType\n}\n```\n\n**Constants** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/constants.go`):\n```go\nAnnotationKeyRuntime = \"agentcube.io/runtime\"\nAnnotationKeyVersion = \"agentcube.io/version\"\n```\n\n### 4. Testing Frameworks/Patterns in Use\n\n**Go Testing:**\n- Standard library `testing` package\n- `github.com/stretchr/testify` -- `assert` and `require` for assertions\n- `net/http/httptest` -- HTTP handler testing (router, picod server)\n- Table-driven tests where applicable\n- Mock objects via interfaces (e.g., `mockLoadBalancer` in router tests)\n- DeepCopy isolation tests for all CRD types\n\n**Python Testing:**\n- **pytest** as test runner\n- `unittest.mock.MagicMock` and `patch` for HTTP mocking\n- `conftest.py` for shared fixtures\n- `patch.dict(os.environ, ..., clear=True)` for environment isolation\n- Parameterized tests via `@pytest.mark.parametrize`\n\n**Bash Testing:**\n- Custom `assert_pass`, `assert_fail`, `assert_contains` helper functions\n- Helm template rendering validation\n- Makefile dry-run verification\n\n### 5. Controller/Manager Structure\n\n**SandboxReconciler** (`pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/reconciler.go`):\n- Custom informer-based reconciler (NOT controller-runtime based)\n- Watches: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, and Pod resources\n- Uses `workqueue.RateLimitingInterface` with exponential backoff\n- Manages session store (Redis/Valkey) synchronization\n- `WatchSandboxOnce()` -- blocking watch for sandbox readiness\n- Event handlers register Add/Update/Delete for all watched resources\n\n**CodeInterpreter Reconciler** (`pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/codeinterpreter.go`):\n- Reconciles CodeInterpreter CR changes\n- Handles deletion (cleans up session store)\n- Syncs CR status to session store\n- Supports warm pool activation\n\n**Agentd Reconciler** (`pkg/agentd/reconciler.go`):\n- Uses **controller-runtime** (`sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime`)\n- Implements idle cleanup for Sandbox resources\n- Checks `last-activity-time` annotation, deletes if expired\n\n### 6. Relevant Configuration Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `go.mod` | Go module: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`, Go 1.25.0, key deps: k8s.io/api v0.34.1, controller-runtime v0.22.2, gin v1.10.0, redis/go-redis v9, testify v1.11.1 |\n| `Makefile` | Build targets for 4 binaries (router, workloadmanager, agentd, picod), Docker builds, test, lint, helm, python targets |\n| `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` | E2E tests on Kind cluster |\n| `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` | Go coverage with Codecov upload |\n| `.github/workflows/main.yml` | Docker build for workloadmanager |\n| `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | golangci-lint |\n| `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK pytest |\n| `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` | Python linting (ruff) |\n| `testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md` | TDD contract defining minimum test sets per component |\n| `design.md` | Python SDK unit test design (618 lines, detailed API contracts, mock strategies) |\n| `deployment/design.md` | Helm chart design, RBAC, Dockerfiles, Makefile reference |\n| `manifests/charts/base/` | Helm chart with CRDs for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter |\n\n### 7. Key Architectural Components\n\n**Four Go Binaries:**\n1. **workloadmanager** -- Control plane API; creates/deletes sandbox sessions; HTTP handlers + reconciler\n2. **router** -- Data plane reverse proxy; JWT auth; load balancing across sandbox pods; session routing\n3. **agentd** -- Idle cleanup controller; watches Sandbox resources and deletes expired ones\n4. **picod** -- Code execution daemon running inside sandbox pods; executes code/commands; file operations\n\n**Session Store:**\n- Interface-based store (`pkg/store/store.go`)\n- Two implementations: Redis (`store_redis.go`) and Valkey (`store_valkey.go`)\n- Codec for serialization\n\n**Client-Go:**\n- Generated via `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1\n- Clientset, listers, and informers for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n- Covers both CodeInterpreter and AgentRuntime resources\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_28462749fffe24OuNK046Kmx0L","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775895415645,"end":1775895645802}}}}
