{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895656324,"sessionID":"ses_28462a26bffeq8oXJ4B2HFgoq1","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba132d2001btuSQhs03SOMWB","messageID":"msg_d7ba12920001ES5MAiwHGW6yPl","sessionID":"ses_28462a26bffeq8oXJ4B2HFgoq1","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_6cb46820e0c2498894a90837","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","limit":80},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-040: Python SDK/CLI 单元测试 — Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: This AR covers comprehensive Python unit tests for the `agentcube-sdk` package (`sdk-python/`). The SDK provides high-level Python clients for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads.\n8: \n9: ### 1.2 Scope\n10: \n11: | Module | File | Lines | Test File | Status |\n12: |--------|------|-------|-----------|--------|\n13: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` | 161 | `tests/test_code_interpreter.py` | **Partial** — 635 lines, but 3 methods missing `test_` prefix (won't run) |\n14: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` | 79 | `tests/test_agent_runtime.py` | **Good** — 837 lines |\n15: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` | 96 | `tests/test_control_plane.py` | **Good** — 370 lines |\n16: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | 176 | `tests/test_data_plane.py` | **Good** — 641 lines |\n17: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | 80 | `tests/test_agent_runtime.py` | **Good** |\n18: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes | 21 | `tests/test_exceptions.py` | **Good** — 77 lines |\n19: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` | 14 | `tests/test_utils.py` | **Good** |\n20: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` | 7 | `tests/test_utils.py` | **Partial** — missing edge cases |\n21: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` | 17 | `tests/test_utils.py` | **Partial** — missing handler reuse test |\n22: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports | 5 | `tests/test_imports.py` | **Good** — 55 lines |\n23: | `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Client re-exports | 6 | `tests/test_imports.py` | **Good** |\n24: \n25: ### 1.3 System Context\n26: \n27: ```\n28: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n29: │                        Python SDK (agentcube)                        │\n30: │                                                                       │\n31: │  ┌──────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     │\n32: │  │  CodeInterpreterClient│     │     AgentRuntimeClient        │     │\n33: │  │  (high-level facade)  │     │   (high-level facade)         │     │\n34: │  └───────┬──────────────┘     └──────────┬────────────────────┘     │\n35: │          │                               │                           │\n36: │  ┌───────▼──────────────┐     ┌──────────▼────────────────────┐     │\n37: │  │  ControlPlaneClient  │     │  AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient  │     │\n38: │  │  (Workload Manager)  │     │   (Router — Agent Runtime)    │     │\n39: │  └──────────────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────┘     │\n40: │          │                                                       │\n41: │  ┌───────▼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n42: │  │           CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient                      │  │\n43: │  │              (Router — Code Interpreter)                      │  │\n44: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n45: │                                                                       │\n46: │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n47: │  │                    Utilities                                   │  │\n48: │  │  create_session  │  read_token_from_file  │  get_logger       │  │\n49: │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n50: │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n51: │  │                   Exceptions                                   │  │\n52: │  │  AgentCubeError → CommandExecutionError                       │  │\n53: │  │                 → SessionError                                │  │\n54: │  │                 → DataPlaneError                              │  │\n55: │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n56: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n57:          │                                              │\n58:          ▼                                              ▼\n59: ┌──────────────────┐                        ┌──────────────────────┐\n60: │  Workload Manager│                        │      Router           │\n61: │  (Control Plane) │                        │  (Data Plane)         │\n62: │  K8s API Server  │                        │  HTTP proxy to pods   │\n63: └──────────────────┘                        └──────────────────────┘\n64: ```\n65: \n66: ### 1.4 Design Principles\n67: \n68: - **Mock at the boundary**: All HTTP calls are mocked via `MagicMock` on `session.post/get/delete/request`. No real network calls.\n69: - **`unittest.mock.patch`**: Used for class-level and function-level patching. Consistent with existing test patterns.\n70: - **Environment isolation**: Tests that depend on env vars use `patch.dict(os.environ, ...)` with `clear=True`.\n71: - **Resource cleanup**: Every test that creates a client calls `client.close()` or `client.stop()` to release HTTP sessions.\n72: - **Table-driven patterns**: Where applicable (e.g., language aliases, timeout variants), use parameterized approaches.\n73: \n74: ### 1.5 Package Structure (test files)\n75: \n76: ```\n77: python-sdk/tests/\n78: ├── __init__.py                          # Package marker\n79: ├── conftest.py                          # Shared fixtures (mock_requests_session, mock_create_session)\n80: ├── test_imports.py                      # Package import and __all__ verification\n\n(Showing lines 1-80 of 618. Use offset=81 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-040: Python SDK/CLI 单元测试 — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis AR covers comprehensive Python unit tests for the `agentcube-sdk` package (`sdk-python/`). The SDK provides high-level Python clients for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads.\n\n### 1.2 Scope\n\n| Module | File | Lines | Test File | Status |\n|--------|------|-------|-----------|--------|\n| `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` | 161 | `tests/test_code_interpreter.py` | **Partial** — 635 lines, but 3 methods missing `test_` prefix (won't run) |\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` | 79 | `tests/test_agent_runtime.py` | **Good** — 837 lines |\n| `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` | 96 | `tests/test_control_plane.py` | **Good** — 370 lines |\n| `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | 176 | `tests/test_data_plane.py` | **Good** — 641 lines |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | 80 | `tests/test_agent_runtime.py` | **Good** |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes | 21 | `tests/test_exceptions.py` | **Good** — 77 lines |\n| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` | 14 | `tests/test_utils.py` | **Good** |\n| `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` | 7 | `tests/test_utils.py` | **Partial** — missing edge cases |","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775895656317,"end":1775895656323}}}}
