{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775895687190,"sessionID":"ses_28462a26bffeq8oXJ4B2HFgoq1","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba1b014001LSk2kVLWfXXfmy","messageID":"msg_d7ba1a93c001pcDJGyI4KUm7zn","sessionID":"ses_28462a26bffeq8oXJ4B2HFgoq1","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895809127,"sessionID":"ses_28462a26bffeq8oXJ4B2HFgoq1","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba1b922001dLdKes2UN82Lua","messageID":"msg_d7ba1a93c001pcDJGyI4KUm7zn","sessionID":"ses_28462a26bffeq8oXJ4B2HFgoq1","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_29cef2fd2a504d3da9fb933b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-041: E2E 集成测试 — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis AR covers end-to-end integration tests for the AgentCube system, validating the full request lifecycle across all four binaries (workloadmanager, router, agentd, picod) running in a real Kind Kubernetes cluster. Tests exercise CRD creation, sandbox lifecycle, reverse proxy routing, JWT authentication, session store synchronization, and idle cleanup.\n\n### 1.2 Scope\n\n| Component | Coverage | Test Type |\n|-----------|----------|-----------|\n| `test/e2e/` | Full system E2E | Kind cluster, real binaries, real CRDs |\n| `test/e2e/framework/` | Test framework utilities | Cluster setup, client helpers, assertions |\n| `test/e2e/suites/` | Test scenario groups | Sandbox lifecycle, proxy, auth, cleanup |\n| `test/e2e/fixtures/` | CRD YAML fixtures | AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter manifests |\n| `Makefile` | `e2e`, `e2e-clean` targets | CI integration |\n\n### 1.3 System Context\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                          Kind Cluster                                    │\n│                                                                          │\n│  ┌──────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  workloadmgr │───▶│  K8s API Server  │◀───│     agentd            │  │\n│  │  (Gin HTTP)  │    │  (etcd)          │    │  (controller-runtime) │  │\n│  └──────┬───────┘    └────────┬─────────┘    └──────────────────────┘  │\n│         │                     │                                         │\n│         │              ┌──────▼──────────┐                              │\n│         │              │   Sandbox Pods   │◀──── picod (sidecar)        │\n│         │              │  (code-interp /  │                              │\n│         │              │   agent-runtime) │                              │\n│         │              └──────┬───────────┘                              │\n│         │                     │                                          │\n│  ┌──────▼───────┐    ┌────────▼─────────┐    ┌──────────────────────┐  │\n│  │    router    │───▶│  Session Store   │    │   Informers/Watchers │  │\n│  │  (Gin proxy) │    │  (Redis/Valkey)  │    │   (client-go)        │  │\n│  └──────────────┘    └──────────────────┘    └──────────────────────┘  │\n│                                                                          │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n         ▲\n         │  HTTP requests (curl / Go http.Client)\n         │\n  ┌──────┴──────┐\n  │  E2E Test   │\n  │  Runner     │\n  └─────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1.4 Design Principles\n\n- **Real cluster, real binaries**: Tests run against actual binaries deployed in Kind, not mocks.\n- **CRD-first**: All sandbox operations go through CRD creation/deletion, mirroring production.\n- **Idempotent**: Each test creates uniquely named resources (UUID-suffixed) and cleans up on exit.\n- **Fail-fast with diagnostics**: On failure, capture pod logs, events, and store state before teardown.\n- **Deterministic timeouts**: All waits use explicit deadlines; no infinite blocks.\n- **Sequential by default**: Tests run sequentially to avoid resource contention; parallel groups where safe.\n\n### 1.5 Test Framework Structure\n\n```\ntest/e2e/\n├── run_e2e.sh                          # Entry script: build, load images, deploy, run tests\n├── main.go                             # Go test entry point (TestMain with setup/teardown)\n├── framework/\n│   ├── cluster.go                      # Kind cluster lifecycle (create, delete, kubeconfig)\n│   ├── deploy.go                       # Helm install, binary image loading, CRD apply\n│   ├── clients.go                      # K8s clientset, dynamic client, REST client builders\n│   ├── wait.go                         # Polling helpers (wait for pod ready, CR status, HTTP)\n│   ├── http.go                         # HTTP client with retry, port-forward helpers\n│   ├── cleanup.go                      # Resource cleanup tracker (defer-based)\n│   └── assertions.go                   # Custom assert helpers (Eventually, Consistently)\n├── suites/\n│   ├── sandbox_lifecycle/\n│   │   ├── suite_test.go               # Ginkgo suite bootstrap\n│   │   ├── create_test.go              # Create AgentRuntime / CodeInterpreter sandboxes\n│   │   ├── status_test.go              # Verify CR status transitions (pending → running)\n│   │   └── delete_test.go              # Delete sandbox, verify cleanup\n│   ├── proxy/\n│   │   ├── suite_test.go\n│   │   ├── routing_test.go             # Router forwards to correct sandbox pod\n│   │   ├── session_test.go             # Session ID propagation, last-activity updates\n│   │   └── multi_endpoint_test.go      # Multiple entry points, path-based routing\n│   ├── auth/\n│   │   ├── suite_test.go\n│   │   ├── jwt_test.go                 # JWT generation, validation, expiry\n│   │   └── rbac_test.go                # ServiceAccount token, namespace isolation\n│   ├── store/\n│   │   ├── suite_test.go\n│   │   └── sync_test.go                # Session store consistency across components\n│   └── agentd/\n│       ├── suite_test.go\n│       └── idle_cleanup_test.go        # Idle timeout triggers sandbox deletion\n└── fixtures/\n    ├── agentruntime.yaml               # Minimal AgentRuntime CR for testing\n    ├── codeinterpreter.yaml            # Minimal CodeInterpreter CR for testing\n    ├── codeinterpreter-warmpool.yaml   # CodeInterpreter with warmPoolSize > 0\n    └── codeinterpreter-picod-auth.yaml # CodeInterpreter with authMode: picod\n```\n\n### 1.6 Technology Choices\n\n| Component | Choice | Rationale |\n|-----------|--------|-----------|\n| Test framework | **Ginkgo + Gomega** | BDD-style, built-in `Eventually`/`Consistently` for async assertions, widely used in K8s ecosystem |\n| Cluster | **Kind v0.30.0** | Matches CI workflow, fast startup, Docker-based |\n| Image loading | `kind load docker-image` | Pre-built images loaded into cluster nodes |\n| Deployment | **Helm** (`helm install`) | Same chart as production, tests chart correctness too |\n| Port-forward | `kubectl port-forward` | Access in-cluster services from test runner |\n| HTTP client | Go `net/http` + retry | Direct HTTP calls to workloadmanager and router |\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 Test Environment Config\n\n```go\ntype TestEnv struct {\n    KubeConfigPath   string        // Path to Kind kubeconfig\n    ClusterName      string        // Kind cluster name (default: agentcube-e2e)\n    Namespace        string        // Test namespace (auto-generated with UUID suffix)\n    Registry         string        // Docker registry for images\n    ImageTag         string        // Image tag (default: e2e-test)\n    WorkloadMgrURL   string        // workloadmanager service URL (after port-forward)\n    RouterURL        string        // router service URL (after port-forward)\n    StoreType        string        // \"redis\" or \"valkey\"\n    EnableAuth       bool          // Whether auth is enabled in deployment\n}\n```\n\n### 2.2 Test Fixture Types\n\n```go\ntype SandboxFixture struct {\n    Name         string            // CR name (unique per test)\n    Namespace    string            // Target namespace\n    Kind         string            // \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n    Image        string            // Container image for sandbox pod\n    Ports        []TargetPort      // Exposed ports\n    AuthMode     string            // \"picod\" or \"none\"\n    WarmPoolSize *int32            // Optional warm pool configuration\n    Labels       map[string]string // Additional labels\n}\n\ntype SandboxResult struct {\n    SessionID   string        // Returned session ID\n    SandboxID   string        // K8s UID of created sandbox\n    SandboxName string        // Generated sandbox name\n    EntryPoints []EntryPoint  // Resolved entry points\n    PodIP       string        // Pod IP address\n    Status      string        // Final status (\"running\", \"failed\", etc.)\n}\n```\n\n### 2.3 Cleanup Tracker\n\n```go\ntype CleanupTracker struct {\n    mu       sync.Mutex\n    resources []cleanupFunc // Functions to call during teardown\n}\n\ntype cleanupFunc struct {\n    name string\n    fn   func() error\n}\n\n// Usage:\n// ct := NewCleanupTracker()\n// defer ct.Cleanup()\n// ct.Add(\"delete-sandbox\", func() error { return client.Delete(...) })\n```\n\n### 2.4 Assertion Helpers (Gomega matchers)\n\n```go\n// Custom matchers\nfunc BeRunningStatus() types.GomegaMatcher\nfunc HaveSessionID() types.GomegaMatcher\nfunc HaveEntryPointWithPath(path string) types.GomegaMatcher\nfunc MatchHTTPStatus(code int) types.GomegaMatcher\n```\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 Workload Manager Endpoints (tested via E2E)\n\n| Method | Path | Request Body | Success Response | Error Codes |\n|--------|------|-------------|------------------|-------------|\n| POST | `/v1/agent-runtime` | `{\"kind\":\"AgentRuntime\",\"name\":\"<cr-name>\",\"namespace\":\"<ns>\"}` | `200 {sessionId, sandboxId, sandboxName, entryPoints}` | 400 (invalid), 404 (CR not found), 500 (internal) |\n| POST | `/v1/code-interpreter` | `{\"kind\":\"CodeInterpreter\",\"name\":\"<cr-name>\",\"namespace\":\"<ns>\"}` | `200 {sessionId, sandboxId, sandboxName, entryPoints}` | 400, 404, 500 |\n| DELETE | `/v1/sessions/{sessionId}` | — | `200 {\"message\":\"session deleted\"}` | 404 (not found), 500 |\n\n### 3.2 Router Endpoints (tested via E2E)\n\n| Method | Path | Headers | Behavior |\n|--------|------|---------|----------|\n| ANY | `/invoke/agent-runtime/{namespace}/{name}/*path` | `x-agentcube-session-id` (optional) | Resolves sandbox, proxies to pod, sets `x-agentcube-session-id` response header |\n| ANY | `/invoke/code-interpreter/{namespace}/{name}/*path` | `x-agentcube-session-id` (optional) | Same as above for CodeInterpreter |\n\n### 3.3 Expected E2E Flow\n\n```\n1. E2E test applies AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter CR via kubectl\n2. Test waits for CR to be recognized by informers (reconciler sync)\n3. Test POSTs to workloadmanager /v1/agent-runtime or /v1/code-interpreter\n4. workloadmanager creates Sandbox CR, watches for Running status\n5. workloadmanager stores session in Redis, returns entry points\n6. Test sends HTTP request to router /invoke/... endpoint\n7. Router resolves session from store, generates JWT, proxies to sandbox pod\n8. Sandbox pod (picod) responds; router forwards response back\n9. Test verifies response headers, session ID, status code\n10. Test deletes session, verifies cleanup\n```\n\n## 4. Error Handling\n\n### 4.1 Test-Level Error Handling\n\n| Scenario | Handling Strategy |\n|----------|-------------------|\n| Kind cluster creation fails | Abort all tests, print `kind create cluster` logs |\n| Image load fails | Abort, show `docker build` and `kind load` output |\n| Helm install fails | Abort, show `helm install` stderr and `kubectl get events` |\n| Pod fails to start | Capture pod describe, logs, events; fail specific test |\n| HTTP request timeout | Retry up to 3 times with exponential backoff; fail with captured state |\n| CRD not recognized | Wait up to 30s for CRD establishment; fail if not ready |\n| Store connection refused | Check Redis/Valkey pod status; fail with diagnostics |\n\n### 4.2 Per-Test Error Recovery\n\n```go\n// Each test follows this pattern:\nIt(\"creates a sandbox and proxies request\", func() {\n    // Setup\n    fixture := createFixture()\n    cleanup.Add(\"delete-cr\", func() error { return deleteCR(fixture) })\n\n    // Act\n    result, err := createSandbox(fixture)\n    Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\n    // Verify\n    Eventually(func() error {\n        return verifySandboxRunning(result.SandboxName)\n    }, 2*time.Minute, 5*time.Second).Should(Succeed())\n\n    // Proxy test\n    resp, err := routerClient.Invoke(result.SessionID, \"/health\")\n    Expect(resp.StatusCode).To(Equal(200))\n\n    // Cleanup is deferred\n})\n```\n\n### 4.3 Diagnostic Collection on Failure\n\n```go\n// Collected on test failure (Ginkgo AfterEach with Failed status):\nfunc CollectDiagnostics(namespace string) {\n    // kubectl get events -n <namespace>\n    // kubectl get pods -n <namespace> -o wide\n    // kubectl logs <workloadmanager-pod> -n <namespace>\n    // kubectl logs <router-pod> -n <namespace>\n    // kubectl logs <agentd-pod> -n <namespace>\n    // kubectl logs <sandbox-pod> -n <namespace>\n    // kubectl exec <redis-pod> -- redis-cli keys \"*\"\n    // Save to $ARTIFACTS_PATH/<test-name>/\n}\n```\n\n## 5. Testing Strategy\n\n### 5.1 Test Suites\n\n#### Suite 1: Sandbox Lifecycle (`suites/sandbox_lifecycle/`)\n\n| Test ID | Name | Steps | Expected |\n|---------|------|-------|----------|\n| E2E-SL-01 | Create AgentRuntime sandbox | Apply AgentRuntime CR → POST /v1/agent-runtime → wait for Running | 200 response with valid sessionId, sandboxName, entryPoints |\n| E2E-SL-02 | Create CodeInterpreter sandbox | Apply CodeInterpreter CR → POST /v1/code-interpreter → wait for Running | 200 response with valid sessionId, entryPoints with port 8080 |\n| E2E-SL-03 | Create CodeInterpreter with warm pool | Apply CodeInterpreter (warmPoolSize=2) → POST /v1/code-interpreter | Creates SandboxClaim, returns session |\n| E2E-SL-04 | Create with picod auth mode | Apply CodeInterpreter (authMode: picod) → POST /v1/code-interpreter | Sandbox has PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY env var |\n| E2E-SL-05 | Duplicate session handling | Create sandbox → Create again with same CR name | Returns existing session or 409 |\n| E2E-SL-06 | Delete sandbox | Create sandbox → DELETE /v1/sessions/{sessionId} | 200 response, Sandbox CR deleted, store entry removed |\n| E2E-SL-07 | Delete non-existent session | DELETE /v1/sessions/{nonexistent-id} | 404 response |\n| E2E-SL-08 | Create with missing CR | POST /v1/agent-runtime with non-existent CR name | 404 response |\n| E2E-SL-09 | Create with invalid request | POST /v1/agent-runtime with empty body | 400 response |\n| E2E-SL-10 | Sandbox status transition | Create sandbox → poll CR status | Status transitions: pending → running within 2 minutes |\n\n#### Suite 2: Proxy Routing (`suites/proxy/`)\n\n| Test ID | Name | Steps | Expected |\n|---------|------|-------|----------|\n| E2E-PR-01 | Proxy to AgentRuntime | Create AgentRuntime sandbox → GET /invoke/agent-runtime/{ns}/{name}/health | 200, response from sandbox pod |\n| E2E-PR-02 | Proxy to CodeInterpreter | Create CodeInterpreter sandbox → GET /invoke/code-interpreter/{ns}/{name}/health | 200, response from sandbox pod |\n| E2E-PR-03 | Session ID propagation | Invoke sandbox → check response headers | `x-agentcube-session-id` header present and matches |\n| E2E-PR-04 | Path-based routing | Sandbox with multiple entry points → invoke different paths | Request routed to correct port based on path prefix |\n| E2E-PR-05 | Last-activity update | Invoke sandbox → check store | `lastActivityAt` updated in Redis |\n| E2E-PR-06 | On-demand sandbox creation | Invoke without session ID (no existing session) | Router creates sandbox via workloadmanager, returns proxied response |\n| E2E-PR-07 | Proxy with invalid session | Invoke with non-existent session ID | 404 response |\n| E2E-PR-08 | Proxy to unreachable sandbox | Create sandbox, kill pod → invoke | 502 or 504 response, not crash |\n| E2E-PR-09 | Header forwarding | Invoke sandbox → check forwarded headers on sandbox side | `X-Forwarded-For`, `X-Forwarded-Host`, `X-Forwarded-Proto` present |\n| E2E-PR-10 | Concurrent proxy requests | Send 10 concurrent requests to same sandbox | All succeed, no data race |\n\n#### Suite 3: Authentication (`suites/auth/`)\n\n| Test ID | Name | Steps | Expected |\n|---------|------|-------|----------|\n| E2E-AT-01 | JWT in proxy request | Create sandbox → invoke → check JWT in proxied request | JWT present with valid session_id claim |\n| E2E-AT-02 | PicoD auth validation | Create CodeInterpreter with picod auth → execute code via proxy | 200, code executes successfully |\n| E2E-AT-03 | Invalid JWT rejection | Send request with malformed JWT to picod | 401 from picod |\n| E2E-AT-04 | ServiceAccount token auth | Create sandbox with SA token in Authorization header | 200, sandbox created with user-scoped client |\n| E2E-AT-05 | Missing auth token | Create sandbox without Authorization header (auth enabled) | 401 response |\n\n#### Suite 4: Session Store (`suites/store/`)\n\n| Test ID | Name | Steps | Expected |\n|---------|------|-------|----------|\n| E2E-ST-01 | Store consistency after create | Create sandbox → query store directly | Session exists with correct sandboxId, entryPoints, status=running |\n| E2E-ST-02 | Store cleanup after delete | Delete session → query store | Session entry removed |\n| E2E-ST-03 | Reconciler sync to store | Modify CR externally → wait for reconcile | Store reflects CR status change |\n| E2E-ST-04 | Store survives pod restart | Restart workloadmanager → query store | Sessions persist (Redis-backed) |\n\n#### Suite 5: Agentd Idle Cleanup (`suites/agentd/`)\n\n| Test ID | Name | Steps | Expected |\n|---------|------|-------|----------|\n| E2E-AC-01 | Idle timeout triggers deletion | Create sandbox → wait without activity → check sandbox | Sandbox deleted after idle timeout |\n| E2E-AC-02 | Activity resets idle timer | Create sandbox → invoke (updates lastActivityAt) → wait | Sandbox NOT deleted (timer reset) |\n| E2E-AC-03 | Max session duration | Create sandbox with short TTL → wait | Sandbox deleted after max duration |\n\n### 5.2 Test Execution Flow\n\n```\nrun_e2e.sh:\n  1. Build all Go binaries (make build)\n  2. Build Docker images (make docker)\n  3. Create Kind cluster (kind create cluster --name agentcube-e2e)\n  4. Load images into Kind (kind load docker-image ...)\n  5. Install Redis/Valkey (helm install redis ...)\n  6. Deploy AgentCube (helm install agentcube manifests/charts/base/)\n  7. Wait for all pods ready (kubectl wait --for=condition=Ready)\n  8. Run Go E2E tests (go test ./test/e2e/... -v -timeout 30m)\n  9. On failure: collect diagnostics to $ARTIFACTS_PATH\n  10. Clean up (make e2e-clean)\n```\n\n### 5.3 Makefile Targets\n\n```makefile\n# Add to existing Makefile:\n\n.PHONY: e2e e2e-clean\n\nE2E_TIMEOUT ?= 30m\nE2E_ARTIFACTS ?= $(shell pwd)/e2e-logs\n\ne2e:\n\t$(Q)bash test/e2e/run_e2e.sh\n\ne2e-clean:\n\t$(Q)kind delete cluster --name agentcube-e2e 2>/dev/null || true\n\t$(Q)rm -rf $(E2E_ARTIFACTS)\n```\n\n### 5.4 Entry Script (`test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nCLUSTER_NAME=\"agentcube-e2e\"\nREGISTRY=\"${REGISTRY:-agentcube}\"\nTAG=\"${TAG:-e2e-test}\"\nARTIFACTS_PATH=\"${ARTIFACTS_PATH:-$(pwd)/e2e-logs}\"\nNAMESPACE=\"agentcube-e2e-$(date +%s)\"\n\necho \"=== AgentCube E2E Tests ===\"\necho \"Cluster: ${CLUSTER_NAME}\"\necho \"Registry: ${REGISTRY}\"\necho \"Tag: ${TAG}\"\necho \"Artifacts: ${ARTIFACTS_PATH}\"\n\n# Step 1: Build images\necho \"--- Building Docker images ---\"\nmake docker TAG=\"${TAG}\" REGISTRY=\"${REGISTRY}\"\n\n# Step 2: Create Kind cluster\necho \"--- Creating Kind cluster ---\"\nkind create cluster --name \"${CLUSTER_NAME}\" --wait 60s\n\n# Step 3: Load images\necho \"--- Loading images into Kind ---\"\nfor img in agentcube router picod; do\n  kind load docker-image \"${REGISTRY}/${img}:${TAG}\" --name \"${CLUSTER_NAME}\"\ndone\n\n# Step 4: Deploy dependencies (Redis)\necho \"--- Deploying Redis ---\"\nhelm install redis bitnami/redis --set auth.enabled=false --wait\n\n# Step 5: Deploy AgentCube\necho \"--- Deploying AgentCube ---\"\nhelm install agentcube manifests/charts/base/ \\\n  --set image.registry=\"${REGISTRY}\" \\\n  --set image.tag=\"${TAG}\" \\\n  --set workloadmanager.store.type=\"redis\" \\\n  --set workloadmanager.store.redis.host=\"redis-master\" \\\n  --set router.store.type=\"redis\" \\\n  --set router.store.redis.host=\"redis-master\" \\\n  --namespace \"${NAMESPACE}\" --create-namespace --wait\n\n# Step 6: Wait for readiness\necho \"--- Waiting for pods ---\"\nkubectl wait --for=condition=Ready pods --all -n \"${NAMESPACE}\" --timeout=120s\n\n# Step 7: Run E2E tests\necho \"--- Running E2E tests ---\"\nexport E2E_NAMESPACE=\"${NAMESPACE}\"\nexport E2E_CLUSTER_NAME=\"${CLUSTER_NAME}\"\nexport ARTIFACTS_PATH=\"${ARTIFACTS_PATH}\"\n\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -timeout \"${E2E_TIMEOUT}\" \\\n  -ginkgo.v \\\n  -ginkgo.junit-report=\"${ARTIFACTS_PATH}/e2e-junit.xml\"\n\necho \"=== E2E Tests Passed ===\"\n```\n\n### 5.5 Fixture Files\n\n#### `fixtures/agentruntime.yaml`\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: AgentRuntime\nmetadata:\n  name: test-agent-runtime\n  namespace: default\nspec:\n  ports:\n    - name: http\n      port: 8080\n      protocol: HTTP\n      pathPrefix: /\n  template:\n    labels:\n      app: test-agent\n    spec:\n      containers:\n        - name: agent\n          image: nginx:1.25-alpine\n          ports:\n            - containerPort: 8080\n          readinessProbe:\n            httpGet:\n              path: /\n              port: 8080\n            initialDelaySeconds: 2\n            periodSeconds: 5\n  sessionTimeout: 15m\n  maxSessionDuration: 1h\n```\n\n#### `fixtures/codeinterpreter.yaml`\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: CodeInterpreter\nmetadata:\n  name: test-code-interpreter\n  namespace: default\nspec:\n  ports:\n    - name: http\n      port: 8080\n      protocol: HTTP\n      pathPrefix: /\n  template:\n    image: nginx:1.25-alpine\n    imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n    command: [\"nginx\", \"-g\", \"daemon off;\"]\n    resources:\n      requests:\n        cpu: 100m\n        memory: 128Mi\n      limits:\n        cpu: 500m\n        memory: 256Mi\n  sessionTimeout: 15m\n  maxSessionDuration: 1h\n  authMode: none\n```\n\n#### `fixtures/codeinterpreter-warmpool.yaml`\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: CodeInterpreter\nmetadata:\n  name: test-code-interpreter-warmpool\n  namespace: default\nspec:\n  ports:\n    - name: http\n      port: 8080\n      protocol: HTTP\n      pathPrefix: /\n  template:\n    image: nginx:1.25-alpine\n    imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n  warmPoolSize: 2\n  sessionTimeout: 15m\n  maxSessionDuration: 1h\n  authMode: none\n```\n\n### 5.6 CI Integration\n\nThe existing `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` already defines the Kind cluster setup and calls `make e2e`. The implementation must ensure:\n\n1. `make e2e` invokes `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`\n2. `make e2e-clean` runs on `always()` (already configured)\n3. Logs are uploaded to `$ARTIFACTS_PATH` on failure (already configured)\n4. Test timeout fits within GitHub Actions job timeout (default 360 minutes)\n\n### 5.7 Test Image Strategy\n\nFor E2E tests, sandbox pods use `nginx:1.25-alpine` as a lightweight, stable HTTP server that:\n- Responds to any path with 200\n- Has a small image footprint (fast Kind load)\n- Is publicly available (no registry auth needed)\n- Supports readiness probes via HTTP GET\n\nFor picod auth tests, a minimal Go HTTP server image is built that:\n- Validates JWT tokens in Authorization header\n- Returns 200 for valid tokens, 401 for invalid\n- Is built from `cmd/picod` or a dedicated test image\n\n### 5.8 Parallelization Strategy\n\nTests run sequentially within each suite to avoid sandbox resource contention. Suites can run in parallel using Ginkgo's `--procs` flag if isolation is guaranteed:\n\n```bash\n# Sequential (default, safe)\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v\n\n# Parallel (requires per-suite namespaces)\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v --ginkgo.procs=4\n```\n\nInitial implementation uses sequential execution for simplicity and reliability. Parallelization can be added once the baseline is stable.\n\n### 5.9 Pre-requisites\n\n| Requirement | Version | Check |\n|-------------|---------|-------|\n| Go | 1.23+ | `go version` |\n| Docker | 24+ | `docker version` |\n| Kind | v0.30.0 | `kind version` |\n| Helm | 3.12+ | `helm version` |\n| kubectl | 1.28+ | `kubectl version` |\n\n### 5.10 Known Limitations\n\n1. **No multi-node testing**: Kind single-node cluster; does not test cross-node networking.\n2. **No TLS testing**: E2E runs without TLS; TLS-specific behavior tested in unit tests.\n3. **No load testing**: E2E validates correctness, not performance. Load tests are separate.\n4. **Image-dependent**: Tests require pre-built images; cannot test against arbitrary commits without building.\n5. **Time-sensitive**: Idle cleanup tests depend on clock; may flake on slow CI runners. Mitigated by using short timeouts (1-2 minutes) in test fixtures.\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/deployment/design-e2e.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/router/main.go\">\nERROR [58:67] server.GetRouter undefined (type *router.Server has no field or method GetRouter)\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/client-go/clientset/versioned/clientset.go\">\nERROR [25:18] could not import github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1 (no required module provides package \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1\")\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-c